== Description ==

The [[Image:Assembly_ConstraintMidPoint.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_ConstraintMidPoint|Mid point]] command constrains the position of a 2D point (such as an end point of a line or an arc, or the center point of a circle or an arc) to the mid point of a straight 2D line.

Line elements are made with [[Image:Workbench_Draft.svg|16px]] [[Draft_Workbench|Draft Workbench]] tools in relation with a [[Image:Assembly_Workplane.svg|16px]] workplane.

== Usage ==

# Select the 2D point to be positioned (or a circle/arc for a center point).
# Select a straight 2D line for its mid point.
# Activate the [[Image:Assembly_ConstraintMidPoint.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_ConstraintMidPoint|Mid point]] command using the:
#* {{Button|[[Image:Assembly_ConstraintMidPoint.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_ConstraintMidPoint|Mid point]]}} button.
# Press the {{Button|[[Image:Assembly3_workbench_icon.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_ResolveConstraints|Solve constraints]]}} or the {{Button|[[Image:Assembly_QuickSolve.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_QuickSolve|Quick solve]]}} button to recompute 
:: (if {{Button|[[Image:Assembly_AutoRecompute.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_AutoRecompute|Auto recompute]]}} and {{Button|[[Image:Assembly_SmartRecompute.svg|16px]] [[Assembly3_SmartRecompute|Smart recompute]]}} are disabled).


